title_full:
Dijit

              —
              Hyperattention - Selected Dijital Works vol 1
            
              (Youth)
label: Youth
description:
Mesmerising debut album of blue and abstracted trip hop from Cairo's Dijit, making their first appearance for Andy Lyster’s YOUTH with a smoked-out, downbeat sound reminding us of Leila’s uber-classic debut album ‘Like Weather', Tricky’s Pre-Millennium Tension, with echoes of Tirzah, ZULI and Msylma.

Perfectly low-lit and charged with a slow, nocturnal... more

label: Duval Timothy
description:
Overdue reissue of Duval Timothy’s sterling debut, recorded in a New York City winter, and finessing a mix of styles nodding to deep techno and classic hip hop with jazzy fluidity and up-to-date trimness. Think Carl Craig meets Pete Rock during a power cut with a piano and bottle of brandy...

label: Nyege Nyege Tapes
description:
Lights out, game over. Duma win 2020. Breathtaking by any measure, Kenyan grindcore band Duma’s unparalleled debut of blast beats, sky-clawing synth noise and scarred larynx vocals is one of the mightiest things you’ll hear all year - a huge RIYL Nkisi, Woid, Senyawa...

Duma's self-titled debut is the most incredible injection of life-affirming, outsider energy... more

label: False Idols
description:
Tricky returns with his 14th studio album, Fall To Pieces, on his own label False Idols.
